\n< Serena >Excuse me. Is there a room available?
I need to rent a place to stay for a while.

\n< Innkeeper >Huh, we have a room available,
how long do you plan to stay?

\n< Serena >I'm not sure yet.
For now, I'd like to go with this.
CommonPopupManager.showInfo({},"Paid 100G.",null)
\n< Innkeeper >Oh?!... Well, well.

\n< Serena >Please also prepare meals and a bed.
If it's not enough, I will pay more.

\n< Innkeeper >Don't worry about any shortages... Even if
you stay for 100 days, it will be
more than enough.
\n< Serena >Is that so?

\n< Serena >By the way, I want to take a bath. Is
there a bath in this inn?

\n< Innkeeper >We have a hot spring in this town,
so you can take a hot bath there.
\n< Serena >Hot springs? Is there such a thing?

\n< Innkeeper >The hot springs are located in a building
to the southwest of the town. If you
leave the inn and walk along the road,
you will arrive there quickly.

\n< Innkeeper >We will have your room ready
for you by the time you return.

\n< Serena >Hmmm...I'll be on my way then.
Take care of the room.

\n< Innkeeper >The room is not ready yet, so please enjoy
the hot springs.
\n< Innkeeper >Good morning. Did you sleep well yesterday?

\n< Serena >Good day. May the blessings of the gods be
upon you... Yes, I seven slept a bit
too much.

\n< Innkeeper >Oh my... Do you have some urgent plans,
perhaps?

\n< Serena >I'm going to the item shop. I need to stop
by for a bit.

\n< Innkeeper >...Is that so. The item shop is located on
the south side of this town.

\n< Innkeeper >If you just walk straight out of this inn,
you will arrive soon.

\n< Serena >I see, thank you. Well then, I'll be
going.
\n< Innkeeper >Take care.
\n< Innkeeper >Are you going to rest?
Yes
No
Yes
No

\n< Innkeeper >We have already received the payment, so
please feel free to use it as you wish.
\n< Serena >Now...did they say it was just south of the city?

\n< Serena >Well... It's not that big of a town. Even if I
don't know, if I walk around and ask,
I'll probably find it soon enough.

\n< Serena >It looks delicious, but I'm not hungry
right now.

\n< Serena >This is the private room for the shop
owners. Let's not go in...
\n< Serena >It's a box.
\n< Serena >Umm... why am I looking into this stuff?
\n< Serena >It's a box.
\n< Serena >I don't see anything particularly useful.
\n< Serena >It's a barrel.

\n< Serena >It seems to contain drinking water. Let's
not touch it.
\n< Serena >It's a fireplace.

\n< Serena >Earlier, I glanced at the guestbook and it seems
that some people stay in the space in
front of this fireplace.

\n< Serena >It's surprising that they're renting out a
place like this, but it's even more
surprising people wants to stay there.
I wonder how they sleep...
\n< Serena >There's a menu and other things written here.
\n< Serena >There's no brioche.

\n< Serena >Should I invest and increase the production?
I'm seriously considering it.
\n< Serena >Please knock before entering.
\n< Serena >....

\n< Serena >Ah, I see. Is someone checking to see if
anyone's inside?
\n< Serena >Is it flour or something?

\n< Serena >It's being kneaded well. It will probably
become delicious bread.
\n< Serena >It's an apple. It's still green.
\n< Serena >I wonder if it will become a cake...
\n< Serena >It's the stove.

\n< Serena >Cooking, huh? Mother might not be pleased, but
I'm a little interested.
\n< Serena >Garlic and onions are hanging.

\n< Serena >These guys are a bad bunch. They must have
received some kind of punishment as a
warning.

\n< Serena >I hope they learn their lesson from this
and become a little nicer.
\n< Serena >There's alcohol placed here.

\n< Serena >I'm not particularly interested, but it
does annoy me a bit when it's placed in
a spot that's clearly out of reach like
that.
\n<Serena> It's a bag of flour.
\n<Serena> I can't seem to lift it.
\n< Serena >Oh, great place.
